text: Fresne-lès-Reims is a former commune. It is in Grand Est in the Marne department in northeast France. On 1 January 2017, it was merged into the new commune of Bourgogne-Fresne.Arrêté préfectoral 27 June 2016 == Related pages == * Communes of the Marne department == References == Category:Former communes in Marne
title: Fresne-lès-Reims
